<P><STRONG>ConnectDots</STRONG> is sample C code illustrating the use of =
OpenGL.=20
&nbsp; It is intended to accompany the book <EM><STRONG>3D Computer =
Graphics: A=20
mathematical approach with OpenGL</STRONG>, </EM>by S. Buss, Cambridge=20
University Press, 2003. &nbsp; However, it can be used independently as=20
well.</P>
<P><STRONG>ConnectDots </STRONG>allows the user to specify points with =
mouse=20
clicks. &nbsp; The points are drawn connected with straight lines.=20
&nbsp;&nbsp;This illustrates how the OpenGL GLUT routines can be used to =
capture=20
mouse clicks.&nbsp; The C code consists of two source files,=20
<STRONG>ConnectDots.c</STRONG> and =
<STRONG>ConnectDots.h.</STRONG>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
