<P><STRONG>Things to try out:</STRONG>=20
<OL>
  <LI>Compile and run the program.&nbsp; Test out the keyboard =
controls.&nbsp;=20
  The left mouse button adds a point.&nbsp; The commands "f" and =
"l"&nbsp;=20
  remove the first and last point from the list of points =
(respectively).&nbsp;=20
  If you go over 64 points, the first point(s) are removed.=20
  <LI>Observe how the program uses an OpenGL GLUT callback to capture =
mouse=20
  clicks and determine their&nbsp; x and y&nbsp; locations.=20
  <LI>Experiment with turning off and on (a) the thick lines and points, =
(b) the=20
  anti-aliasing.&nbsp; What difference does this make to the appearance =
and the=20
  speed of the graphics?&nbsp; Your results may vary widely depending on =
your=20
  implementation of OpenGL.=20
  <LI>MAJOR PROJECT: write a program that generates Catmull-Rom splines =
or=20
  Overhauser splines that interpolate the dots.&nbsp; Do something =
appropriate=20
  at the endpoints to make the first and last points be interpolated. =
</LI></OL>
